\ ---- skip ----
\ basic
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 2 skip .

\ boundaries
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 skip .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 5 skip .

\ clamps
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 99 skip .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] -2 skip .

\ empty source
[ ] 3 skip .

\ set source: yields the trailing portion of the sorted items as an array
< 5 1 3 2 4 > 2 skip .

\ composes
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 skip cardinality .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 1 skip reverse .

\ ---- last ----
\ basic
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 2 last .

\ boundaries
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 last .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 5 last .

\ clamp: n > length yields the whole array
[ 1 2 3 ] 99 last .

\ empty source
[ ] 3 last .

\ skip + last is the identity over a full traversal
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 2 skip 3 last .

\ ---- failures ----
\ skip is built atop take, so its errors surface as take's
[ 1 2 3 ] "x" skip
"x" 2 skip
[ 1 2 3 ] "x" last
"x" 2 last
